Primary Instructor, George Washington University <br><br> Years taught: 2025 <br><br> Designed and taught a four-day bootcamp to incoming PhD students covering probability, descriptive and inferential statistics, calculus, linear regression, and causal inference. Supplemented technical instruction with introductions to R and Stata, discussions of research ethics, and professional guidance on comprehensive exams and course selection.
